# ── AI provider (step ⑤ cost analysis) ──────────────────────────────────────
# The project spec calls this BEDROCK_API_KEY, but the supplied sk-or-v1-… key
# is an OpenRouter key (AWS Bedrock uses SigV4, not a bearer sk- token).
# OpenRouter is OpenAI-compatible, so the backend talks to it through the
# `openai` SDK pointed at https://openrouter.ai/api/v1.
#
# Provide the key WITHOUT quotes. Any of the three names below are accepted;
# BEDROCK_API_KEY is the documented one.
BEDROCK_API_KEY=sk-or-v1-your-key-here

# Optional overrides:
# OPENROUTER_BASE_URL=https://openrouter.ai/api/v1
# AI_MODEL=meta-llama/llama-3.1-8b-instruct

# ── Database (steps ④ / ⑥: history + analysis persistence) ─────────────────
# Azure Managed PostgreSQL (Flexible Server, Sweden Central). Real connection
# string below; tables are auto-created on startup (db.init_db).
# NOTE: this file is git-tracked, so the password lives in git history. Rotate
# it (az postgres flexible-server update -n finopscostdetectivepg -g Finops_Cost_Detective -p <new>)
# and replace here if you ever push this repo publicly.
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://costdetective:73vaDrhoORmngy6ADQ70CKG@finopscostdetectivepg.postgres.database.azure.com:5432/costdetective?sslmode=require
